<!--

How to add an auxiliary UI:

Simply add your panel(s) here, either by hand or procedurally in code (using
setXml/setXmlTable, ideally in the YourModule.onLoad method) and keep the two
following constraints in mind:

1 -	The setup UI relies heavily on setXmlTable to dynamically update its
	contents, erasing any live changes made to any other UI. So don't try to
	update your UI during setup.

2 -	After the setup, other modules may have a live UI that cannot be properly
	preserved via a pair of getXml/setXml calls. So, update your UI only using
	targeted setAttribute/setValue calls.

More generally, take a look at the Example.lua file to see how your code might
be integrated to this mod in a standard way.

-->
